Case_Structure
Class Solution

java.lang.Object
  Case_Structure.Solution

public class Solution
extends java.lang.Object

Object storing the information of a solution type (which must match to at least one of the domains' solution types). This means that the existence of this Solution_Type must be checked in the corresponding Domain before creating an object of this type.

Author:
Marc Bola–os

addComponent

public int addComponent(java.lang.Object value,
                        java.lang.String name,
                        java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> position)
Adds a new solution component at the position given.

Parameters:
value - Object generic representation of the solution value.
name - String with the abstract value identifier/name.
position - ArrayList with the hierarchical position desired (each element is a position in the hierarchy). If is empty then will be inserted in the top level.
Returns:
inserted_pos with the integer position where the new solution has been inserted.
